                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/319: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-24T16:00:00+01:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Department’s circular of June 29, 3 p.m.<note n="75" xml:id="d514fn75">See
                        footnote 71, <ref target="#pg_734">p. 734</ref>.</note> Dutch Government
                    states that before it gives its formal adhesion again to the amended resolution
                    of the United States Government covering shipment of arms and munitions of war
                    to China it desires to learn whether Italian Government has adhered without
                    reservation to the amended resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
